{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"675f8dda-eeb0-48ee-85b4-202294b87a9f","content":"In your `App.xaml.cs`, override `CreateWindow` and subscribe to the lifecycle events:\n\n```csharp\nprotected override Window CreateWindow(IActivationState? activationState)\n{\n    var window = base.CreateWindow(activationState);\n\n    window.Created    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Created\");\n    window.Resumed    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Resumed\");\n    window.Activated  += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Activated\");\n    window.Deactivated += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Deactivated\");\n    window.Stopped    += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Stopped\");\n    window.Destroying += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Destroying\");\n\n    // iOS / Mac Catalyst only — fires when the app is backgrounded\n    window.Backgrounding += (s, e) => Debug.WriteLine(\"Window Backgrounding\");\n\n    return window;\n}\n```\n\n**Typical order on mobile:**\n`Created → Activated → (user switches away) → Deactivated → Stopped → (user returns) → Resumed → Activated → … → Destroying`\n\n> **Note:** `Backgrounding` only fires on iOS/Mac Catalyst and provides a `BackgroundingEventArgs` with a `State` dictionary you can use to persist data for later restoration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"24410e32-f038-44dc-8f0e-7d74bbe6b9f4","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI Window lifecycle events and how to subscribe to them for debugging/logging purposes. This is a general knowledge question — I don't need to search the codebase for this. Let me provide a concise, helpful answer.\n\nIn .NET MAUI, the `Window` class exposes several lifecycle events:\n\n- `Created`\n- `Resumed`\n- `Activated`\n- `Deactivated`\n- `Stopped`\n- `Destroying`\n- `Backgrounding` (iOS/Mac Catalyst)\n\nYou can override `CreateWindow` in your `App` class and subscribe to them.","outputTokens":492,"requestId":"483B:2ADC27:74B3159:81073DB:69F3FB09"},"id":"248eafd9-1a78-4d21-81dd-15e37e9c11d4","timestamp":"2026-05-01T01:00:03.575Z","parentId":"d0fba66a-c03d-44c1-a2fd-346675211ceb"}
